{#def intro="", return_to="/create", default_to_signup=True #}
{#
  Sign-in modal page, hosted in the desktop client's shared modal
  WebContentsView -- the same overlay layer as the other centered modals -- so
  it covers the whole window including the title bar (rather than sitting
  inside the content view like an in-page dialog). Opened from the create
  screen when a signed-out user presses "Create" with the Imbue Cloud preset
  selected, from the welcome splash's Sign Up / Log In buttons, from the home
  screen's account launcher when signed out, and from the Manage Accounts
  modal's "Add account".

  ``default_to_signup`` picks which AuthForm tab is visible on first paint
  (the inline links still flip between them client-side); callers that say
  "Log In" pass mode=signin through the route so the sign-in tab leads.

  Transparent body + a dim backdrop reveal the screen behind it; the
  centered card holds the shared auth form (``auth.AuthForm``). All form
  interactivity lives in ``static/auth.js``; the inline script below tells it
  how to route post-auth navigations: they must land in the *content* view
  behind this overlay and dismiss the modal -- not reload the overlay itself.
  In Electron that goes through ``window.minds``; as a plain standalone page
  (browser fallback) it navigates normally.

  ``intro`` is the explanatory copy shown under each tab heading (why the user
  is being asked to sign in). ``return_to`` is where a successful sign-in (or
  a dismissal without signing in) lands the content view; the route validates
  it as a safe local path before it reaches this template.
#}
{% set _scripts %}
<script src="/_static/auth.js" defer></script>
<script>
  (function () {
    // Where auth.js should land the user after a successful sign-in, and where
    // an email-verification round-trip should return them.
    window.MINDS_AUTH_RETURN_TO = {{ return_to | tojson }};
    // How auth.js performs those navigations. In the Electron modal overlay the
    // form runs in its own WebContentsView, so navigations must target the
    // content view behind the modal (navigateContent also dismisses the modal).
    // Without the bridge (standalone page) we just navigate this page.
    window.MINDS_AUTH_NAV = function (url) {
      if (window.minds && window.minds.navigateContent) window.minds.navigateContent(url);
      else window.location.href = url;
    };

    // Dismiss the overlay without signing in. The close button
    // (DialogCloseButton) calls this by name; Escape is handled by the
    // Electron main process for any modal-view page.
    window.dismissSigninModal = function () {
      if (window.minds && window.minds.closeModal) window.minds.closeModal();
      else window.location.href = window.MINDS_AUTH_RETURN_TO || "/";
    };

    var backdrop = document.getElementById("signin-modal-backdrop");
    if (backdrop) {
      backdrop.addEventListener("click", function (e) {
        if (e.target === backdrop) window.dismissSigninModal();
      });
    }

    // "Forgot password?" must not navigate this overlay iframe: the full-page
    // auth flow would render inside the modal view (over whatever the content
    // view shows) and a sign-in completed there would strand the whole app
    // inside the overlay. Route it through MINDS_AUTH_NAV instead, which
    // lands the page in the content view and dismisses the modal (or, as a
    // standalone page, just navigates).
    var forgotLink = document.querySelector('a[href="/auth/forgot-password"]');
    if (forgotLink) {
      forgotLink.addEventListener("click", function (e) {
        e.preventDefault();
        window.MINDS_AUTH_NAV("/auth/forgot-password");
      });
    }
  })();
</script>
{% endset %}
<OverlaySurface title="Sign in"
                body_style="-webkit-app-region: no-drag;"
                scripts={{ _scripts }}>
  <div id="signin-modal-backdrop" class="fixed inset-0 flex items-center justify-center bg-surface-overlay p-4">
    <div class="relative bg-surface-primary rounded-lg shadow-overlay max-w-md w-full p-8 text-left">
      <DialogCloseButton onclick="dismissSigninModal()" />
      <auth.AuthForm :default_to_signup="default_to_signup" :intro="intro" />
    </div>
  </div>
</OverlaySurface>
